07813nam a22009015i 9780748630868DE-B159720220306030904.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220306t20222007stk    fo  d z      eng d  a97807486308687 a10.1515/97807486308682doi  a(DE-B1597)615139  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  astkcGB-SCT 4aBP173.7b.I8695 2007eb (Online) 7aPOL0370002bisacsh1 aAbbas, Tahir, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aIslamic Political Radicalism :bA European Perspective /cTahir Abbas. 1aEdinburgh : bEdinburgh University Press, c[2022] 4c©2007  a1 online resource (324 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tNotes on the Contributors -- tPreface and Acknowledgements -- tPART I DEFINITIONS -- tCHAPTER 1 Introduction: Islamic Political Radicalism in Western Europe -- tCHAPTER 2 The Discourse of ‘Terrorism’ between Violence, Justice and International order -- tCHAPTER 3 A Clinical Psychology Perspective on Radical Islamic Youth -- tCHAPTER 4 The Scales for Defining Islamic Political Radicalism -- tPART II ISLAMIC POLITICAL RADICALISM IN EUROPE -- tCHAPTER 5 Europe and Political Islam: Encounters of the Twentieth and Twenty-first Centuries -- tCHAPTER 6 Anti-Semitism amongst Muslims -- tCHAPTER 7 The Growth of Islamic Radicalism in Eurasia -- tCHAPTER 8 RADICAL ISLAM IN EUROPE: MISPERCEPTIONS AND MISCONCEPTIONS -- tPart III THE BRITISH CONTEXT -- tCHAPTER 9 How the Zionist Colonisation of Palestine Radicalised British Muslims -- tCHAPTER 10 From the Ethos of Justice to the Ideology of Justice: Understanding Radical Views of Scottish Muslims -- tCHAPTER 11 Islamic Political Radicalism in Britain: The Case of Hizb-ut-Tahrir -- tCHAPTER 12 ISLAMIC POLITICAL RADICALISM IN BRITAIN: MUSLIM MEN IN BRADFORD -- tCHAPTER 13 ‘Because I am Pakistani . . . and I am Muslim . . . I am Political’ – Gendering Political Radicalism: Young Femininities in Bradford -- tCHAPTER 14 Disconnection and Exclusion: Pathways to Radicalisation? -- tCHAPTER 15 Transitional Religiosity Experiences: Contextual Disjuncture and Islamic Political Radicalism -- tCHAPTER 16 An Assessment of Colonial Strategies of Resistance, Liminality and Herberg’s Thesis in the Rise of Radicalism among British South Asian Youth -- tPart IV after 7/7 -- tChapter 17 Ruminations and Reflections on British Muslims and Islam post-7/71 -- tCHAPTER 18 Electronic Monitoring and the Creation of Control Orders for Terrorist Suspects in Britain -- tCHAPTER 19 British Islamic Political Radicalism -- tCHAPTER 20 Disengaging with Terrorism: The Internal Muslim Challenge in Deligitimising Radicalism as a Means of Tackling Extremism -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAnalyses the sociological, anthropological, psychological and political causes and consequences of Islamic political radicalism in EuropeAuthors explore the motivations behind such radicalism, focusing on an array of different factors. These include economic and social alienation, political and cultural marginalisation, gender and masculinity, and psychological issues, both at an individual and community level.Other issues discussed are the state responses, national and international, to the ‘War on Terror’ which came about after the attacks on America in September 2001; and the role of Islamic political organisations and their impact on changing ethno-religious identities. This is considered particularly in relation to concept of the Ummah and its influence on the position of Islam and Muslims in places such as Iraq, Afghanistan, and Palestine, as well as Bosnia, Chechnya, and Kashmir.The authors provide an analysis of events and experiences in different European nation states, with a detailed focus on Britain. This book is particularly relevant in the current climate as an attempt to understand the factors that shape Islamic political radicalism in Europe.Key FeaturesWritten for academics as well as activists and practitionersExplores major new and emerging issues, particularly in the aftermath of the July 2005 London bombings  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2022) 0aIslam and politicszEurope. 0aRadicalismzEurope. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Terrorism.2bisacsh1 aAbbas, Tahir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbdullah, Daud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAwan, Akil N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAziz, Haris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeaves, Ron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamid, Sadek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHellyer, H. A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKazmi, Sayyed Nadeem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLifton, Edward J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacey, Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarranci, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMukhopadhyay, Alok Rashmi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNellis, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNielsen, Jørgen S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPatel, Ismail Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSanghera, Gurchathen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilvestri, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpalek, Basia, econtributor.4ctb4https:/